verbose_text: The protein expression levels of ZO-1 (XREF_FIG; 0.22 +/-0.02 vs. 0.51 +/-0.02; P < 0.01), JAM-1 (XREF_FIG; 0.16 +/-0.02 vs. 0.24 +/-0.03; P < 0.01) and beta-catenin (XREF_FIG; 0.21 +/-0.04 vs. 0.39 +/-0.05; P < 0.01) were significantly reduced in the duodenal tissues of FD rats, compared with those of the control group.
